deck: Jamaica Dyer is the creator of the webcomic Weird Fishes, published in print by SLG.
description:
From Jamaica's website:

 Jamaica Dyer is currently working on freelance Flash animation, illustration and comics. She’s also known to do production design for films, storyboarding and art direction for print. Currently residing in the Bay Area and recently received her BFA in illustration and animation from San Jose State.

Jamaica’s been drawing comics since she was a kid, and has self-published numerous zines and has appeared in various indie anthologies and magazines. In college she’s learned to cultivate her love for visual storytelling in the animation department, and also branch out into the film department, fine art department and English department.

Weird Fishes is her first stab at doing a graphic novel in webcomics. Written, drawn and colored by Jamaica, as heard by Caleb F.
name: Jamaica Dyer

deck: Creator and writer of the independent title THE REJECTS and as well as LEGACY, CRUSADER, and THE TRIUMVIRATE OF THICKETWOOD.
description:
Anthony is a new face in the comic book galaxy, with his first work THE REJECTS garnering positive reviews in its initial limited run. 
 
With a desire to write both prose and for sequential art, Anthony founded the BLACK HOLE CAVALRY: a creative studio and publishing imprint with fellow creators.   
 

With his new grassroots studio running, Anthony collaborated with writing partner Jason Jacobs and artist Apriyadi Kusbiantoro to bring together the child of their collective minds in the form of LEGACY. Still in development the team hopes to have a publisher in place to carry the book sometime in 2011. 
 
In addition to LEGACY, Anthony is collaborating with artist Lexxy Douglass on an all-ages project called THE TRIUMVIRATE OF THICKETWOOD which will also seek publication in the coming year.  
 
Anthony has written the short stories IN DEFENSE OF GREENROCK, THE KINGMAKER, AVA and others which can be found by clicking here. THE KINGMAKER is set to find publication in sci-fi anthology TRIANGULATION this year. 
 
A self-proclaimed "funny guy" (nobody else proclaimed so he took the initiative) Anthony ran the ZOMBIE-BOX website where he edited comic pages to give them humorous twists, titled WAITING FOR WEDNESDAY. 
 
You can catch Anthony on Twitter, and at the Baltimore Comic Con and New York Comic Con this 2011 season.
name: Anthony Ferrante

deck: Award winning fantasy/science-fiction writer, activist and academic.
description:
He refers to his work as "weird fiction", close to steampunk with H.P. Lovecraft horror elements.

China Miéville was also supposed to be the writer of Swamp Thing Volume 5, a series which would be aborted because of DC's change of direction with the new regime of Dan DiDio and Jim Lee as co-publishers.

China began writing the H Dial concept in Dial H which started in July, 2012, part of DC's New 52 but with Vertigo boss Karen Berger as editor per his request. In the series he examined the psychological impact of when a normal person acquires superpowers.
name: China Miéville
